issues.description: The solution’s acceptSupplyDelivery method is declared with default (package-private) visibility, but the problem specification’s UML and method list mark it as public. This visibility mismatch may cause confusion and test failures when invoking the method.
issues.suggested_fix: Add the `public` modifier to the `acceptSupplyDelivery` method in SealSaloon (declare it as `public static void acceptSupplyDelivery(...)`).
